AH 9/17/2015:  Thanks for the image of the painted edge, I do want to use it.  One cover image is missing and the others are out of order, so can they be re-ordered so that the shot of the painted edge, currently body0029, becomes body0025; the first shot of the cover closed, currently body0025, becomes body0026; the second shot of the cover closed, currently body0028, becomes body0027; the shot of the outside of the cover open, currently body0027, becomes body0028; and the shot of the inside of the cover open, *currently missing or not displaying*, becomes body0029?_x000D_
_x000D_
Also photographed "spine", painted edge of MS, as "body0029.tif" 9/15/15 CL_x000D_
_x000D_
First shot should be of the manuscript without its cloth cover but with the palm ties that slide on and off.  After the first shot, please slide off the ties; they do not need to appear in any other shots.  The manuscript is oriented properly if there is a Buddha on the left end of the title page and a diamond pattern on the right end; foliation is in the left margin on the verso side.  After shooting the whole manuscript, the last four files are for images of the cloth cover, on and off the manuscript.  First, two of the manuscript wrapped up, one of the side where the tie is attached and one of the other side.  Finally, two of the cover apart from the manuscript, completely open, one of the red outside with the tie at the top (please arrange the tie above the cover so that it is completely visible but not covering any of the cover) and one of the yellow inside with the tie at the top (tie arranged the same way).

_x000D_
The covers of this manuscript are triangular and so cannot lie flat.  With its cord removed, the manuscript has nothing to hold it together and no stable resting position, so please prop it carefully for taking the pictures of the covers (and the final image of the manuscript from the side -- either side is fine).  Otherwise, the covers do not need to be in the images, and the cord does not need to be photographed at all.  In the correct starting orientation, the gouges with white chalk or pigment will be on the half of the upper cover nearer the reader, and f. 1v will have a dot of white paint on its upper edge when flipped up._x000D_
_x000D_
When repacking the manuscript, please make sure that the inner edges of the light cardboard and the knots of the twine are resting against one of the wood covers, not against the edges of the palm leaves.

Orientation for photography:  the upper cover is the one with the border missing all the way around, f. A01 is blank, and f. A02 is illustrated.  There is missing text at one of the breaks, so in that case, in both directions, there will be an image with only one half of a folio.  The text is continuous through the other break, so in that case, there will be one image showing both halves of the folio, even though there is a break between them.  Both breaks are flagged with directions.  See Amey with questions!
